From: Lizz K <ekopecny@mail.usyd.edu.au>

Malaria doesn't seem to have followed that pattern so far. It's been
essentially eliminated from parts of the USA and Europe (and Northern parts
of Australia) where it was once endemic, but much of the developing world
still suffers and dies.
More to the point, even bednets seem to be less utilised in some malarious
areas than they once were, possibly because they are becoming even less
affordable there!
--
