Date: Wed, 6 Oct 1999 14:55:20 +1000
From: SHEOREY Harsha <SHEOREHS@svhm.org.au>

In the interest of folks in the 'developed world', we (governments, public,
pharmaceutical companies etc) should put in money/resources for research,
diagnosis and therapy into the "less developed world" where most of the
problem is -- before it blows out of proportions and comes back to "bite"
us! After all, isn't this precisely the
principle of Public Health that we teach (and ?practice in the developed
world) -- identify a problem, go to the root of the problem and stop it in
it's path before it spreads?
Hence, I would propose, instead of bringing these diseases back to us, we go
out and tackle them!
--
